INSERT INTO [hlc_DoctorNote] ([ID], [DoctorID], [UserID], [DateEntered], [Notes], [FileName]) VALUES (N'53', N'420', N'admin', N'2011-09-23 22:50:00', N'Dr. Taylor is a native of Greenville, South Carolina. He attended North Carolina State University for undergraduate studies and obtained his medical degree from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill.  He completed a residency in Obstetrics and Gynecology at Carolinas Medical Center and after which he practiced general obstetrics and gynecology for 5 years before pursuing specialized surgical training in Urogynecology and Advanced Pelvic Surgery at Northside Hospital in Atlanta, Georgia.

Dr. Taylor has practiced for 4 years on the faculty at Carolinas Medical Center in the Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology as Director of Minimally Invasive Gynecologic Surgery and Urogynecology. During this time he won numerous teaching awards and published articles in both national and international journals on pelvic organ prolapse. He also lectures both nationally and internationally on topics related to pelvic floor dysfunction and gynecologic surgery. In addition Dr. Taylor has traveled to West Africa where he was trained as a fistula surgeon.

Dr. Taylor’s professional and clinical interests are in minimally invasive gynecologic surgery, pelvic organ prolapse, female urinary and bowel incontinence, vaginal skin disorders, and pelvic pain. 
In addition to his clinical practice Dr. Taylor is a member of the American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologist, American Urogynecology Association, North Carolina Medical Society, North Carolina Obstetrics and Gynecology Society, and American Association of Gynecologic Laparoscopist.

Dr. Taylor has privileges at several area hospitals including Lake Norman Regional Medical Center, Presbyterian Hospitals, and Carolinas Medical Center.
Dr. Taylor is a member of numerous medical societies including the North Carolina Medical Society, North Carolina Obstetrics and Gynecology Society, American College of Obstetrics and Gynecology, American Urogynecologic Society, and is certified in obstetrics and gynecology by the American Board of Obstetrics and Gynecology.', N'')
